@base = https://your-label.eastus.cloudapp.azure.com
@realm = edfi
@key = REPLACE_WITH_SINGLE_TENANT_KEY
@secret = REPLACE_WITH_SINGLE_TENANT_SECRET
# The raw `Basic key:secret` form below is base64-encoded automatically by VS Code REST Client.
# Pre-encode it instead (set `@basic = <base64(key:secret)>`, use `Authorization: Basic {{basic}}`)
# if a secret contains characters REST Client treats as variables ({{ }}) or your client does
# not auto-encode the raw form.

### Discovery (no auth)
GET {{base}}/st-dms

### Get an access token (Basic auth = key:secret) -- shared Keycloak realm (advertised in Discovery)
# @name token
POST {{base}}/auth/realms/{{realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token
Authorization: Basic {{key}}:{{secret}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials

### List schools
GET {{base}}/st-dms/data/ed-fi/schools
Authorization: Bearer {{token.response.body.access_token}}

### Create a school
POST {{base}}/st-dms/data/ed-fi/schools
Authorization: Bearer {{token.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "schoolId": 255901001,
  "nameOfInstitution": "Security Review High School",
  "educationOrganizationCategories": [
    { "educationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/EducationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor#School" }
  ],
  "schoolCategories": [
    { "schoolCategoryDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/SchoolCategoryDescriptor#High School" }
  ],
  "gradeLevels": [
    { "gradeLevelDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/GradeLevelDescriptor#Ninth grade" }
  ]
}
